HEADWORD: Fenerate
<hw>Fen"er*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>faeneratus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>faenerari</ets> lend on interest,
fr. <ets>faenus</ets> interest.]</ety> <def>To put money to usury; to
lend on interest.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Cockeram.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

